data.text:
Is Yesung of Super Junior the third and youngest son of North Korean leader Kim Jong Il?

A Swiss newspaper made a huge mistake when it published the photo of Yesung on its front and inside pages and identified him as Kim Jong-un, the third and youngest son of Kim Jong Il.

The article was published last April 7, 2009, and it talked about Kim Jong-un, who is rumored to be the successor of Kim Jong Il.

The newspaper, Blick am Abend, is a publication in Switzerland, with an estimated circulation of 270,000 copies a day.

Apparently, newspapers and other media don’t know how Kim Jong-un looks like today. He was born in 1984 so he is probably 25 years old.

The Swiss newspaper committed a blunder when it mistook Yesung as Kim Jong-un since Yesung’s real name is Kim Joong-won and he was also born in 1984.
